        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 6:30AM EDT until June 8 at 7:00AM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 630 AM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Green Plain, or
10 miles east of Emporia, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to trees and powerlines.

Locations impacted include...
Courtland, Boykins, Newsoms, Capron, Adams Grove, Handsom, Worrell,
Sunbeam, Mason, Drewryville, Joyner, Shiloh, and Story.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
